headline: Exclusive-Canada defense review makes case for sticking with F-35 jets, sources say
summary: OTTAWA (Reuters) -Canadian defense officials have strongly made the case that Ottawa should stick to a plan to buy 88 Lockheed Martin Corp F-35 fighter jets rather than splitting the order, two sources familiar with the matter said on Thursday.  The final decision rests with the Liberal government of Prime Minister Mark Carney, said the sources, who requested anonymity given the sensitivity of the situation.  Canada unveiled the C$19-billion ($14-billion) deal in early 2023.
